cppcheck
------------------------------------------
This program tries to detect bugs that your C/C++ compiler don't see.
The goal is no false positives.

Your compiler can detect many problems that cppcheck don't try to detect.
It is recommend that you enable as many warnings as possible in your compiler.

Cppcheck is versatile. You can check non-standard code that includes various
compiler extensions, inline assembly code, etc.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.10

Build requirements:
  binutils-20080624-2
  cygport-0.4.4-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  make-3.81-1
  docbook-xsl-1.75.2-1
  libxslt-1.1.24-2
  libpcre-8.02-1

Canonical website:
  http://sourceforge.net/projects/cppcheck

Canonical download:
  http://sourceforge.net/projects/cppcheck/files

